label: A10B3_hP26_176_c3h_h-001
title: Cu$_{10}$Sb$_{3}$ Structure
comments:
(G\"{u}nzel, 1958) place this structure in space group $P\overline{3}$ \#147 but (Cenzual, 1991) showed that all the atoms have $z$ coordinates which are are either 1/4 or 3/4. In that case there is a six-fold rotation axis, making the space group $P6_3/m$ \#176. 
 (Cenzual, 1991) also note that (G\"{u}nzel, 1958) list the $z$ coordinate of the (3d) copper atoms as 1/4, but as seen from the figures it must be 3/4 in their paper, and 1/4 here.
